1 peri od of at least seven (7) years prior to the first January 1 date
2 following the year during which the person attains the age of sixty-
3 five (65) years, shall not exceed the fair cash value placed upon
4 the property during the first year in which the individual head of
5 household was sixty-five (65) years of age or older and had gross
6 household income from all sources which did not exceed an amount as
7 provided in subsection B of this section. For purposes of this
8 section, absence from the homestead for a period not to exceed three
9 hundred sixty-five (365) days during any seven-year period shall not
10 disqualify the owner from eligibility. The provisions of this
11 section shall only be applicable to a homestead with a fair cash
12 value of Seven Hundred Thousand Dollars ($700,000.00) or less. For
13 purposes of this section, the fair cash value shall be determined in
14 the same manner as provided by Section 8B of Article X of the
15 Oklahoma Constitution. Subject to the limitations of this section,
16 the fair cash value shall not exceed such amount as long as the
17 individual head of household who is sixty-five (65) years of age or
18 older owns and occupies the property and as long as the gross
19 household income from all sources does not exceed an amount as
20 provided in subsection B of this section. If any improvements are
21 made to the property, the fair cash value of the improvements shall
22 be assessed in accordance with law by the county assessor and added
23 to the assessed value of the property. Once the fair cash value of
24 the improvements has been added to the fair cash value of the
