7 five (65) years of age or older prior to January 1, 1997, and has
8 gross household income from all sources of Twenty-five Thousand
9 Dollars ($25,000.00) or less in calendar year 1996, the fair cash
10 value of the real property shall be the fair cash value placed upon
11 the property on January 1, 1997. If the individual head of
12 household ceases to own and occupy the property or if the gross
13 household income from all sources exceeds an amount as provided in
14 subsection B of this section, the fair cash value of the property
15 shall be determined as if the provisions of Section 8 of Article X
16 of the Constitution of the State of Oklahoma or any other provisions
17 relating to a limitation on the fair cash value of locally assessed
18 real property had been in effect during the time the property was
19 valued pursuant to the provisions of this section.
20 B. The income threshold for the gross household income from all
21 sources for an individual head of household under this section shall
22 not exceed the amount determined by the United States Department of
23 Housing and Urban Development to be the estimated median income for
24 the preceding year for the county or metropolitan statistical area
