4 SECTION 2. The Ballot Title for the proposed Constitutional
5 amendment as set forth in SECTION 1 of this resolution shall be in
6 the following form:
7 BALLOT TITLE
8 Legislative Referendum No. ____ State Question No. ____
9 THE GIST OF THE PROPOSITION IS AS FOLLOWS:
10 This measure amends Section 8C of Article 10 of the Oklahoma
11 Constitution. Increases in fair cash value of homesteads are
12 limited for individual heads of household age sixty-five (65) or
13 older. The increase cannot exceed the fair cash value of the
14 property during the first year in which the owner was sixty-five
15 (65) years of age or older. This limit applies if the
16 individual head of household meets both the age requirement and
17 an income limit determined by the United States Department of
18 Housing and Urban Development. This measure would eliminate the
19 income limit requirement. The age limit would not change. The
20 person would be required to have occupied the homestead for
21 seven (7) years. A person could be away from the homestead for
22 a period not to exceed three hundred sixty-five (365) days in a
23 seven-year period and still qualify. The limit on increases in
24 fair cash value of homestead property would only apply if the
HJR1081 HFLR Page 4
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 fair cash value of the homestead is Seven Hundred Thousand
2 Dollars ($700,000.00) or less. This value would be determined
3 the same way as it is determined for all other purposes in the
4 property tax system.
5 SHALL THE PROPOSAL BE APPROVED?
6 FOR THE PROPOSAL — YES _____________
7 AGAINST THE PROPOSAL — NO _____________
8 SECTION 3. The Chief Clerk of the House of Representatives,
